article.headline: Evans scores 32, Jackson State knocks off Arkansas State 75-71

images.name: Jackson State punctuates win with Romelle Mansel's slam
images.caption: Jackson State punctuates win with Romelle Mansel's slam

article.linkText: Evans scores 32, Jackson State knocks off Arkansas State 75-71
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- — Ken Evans Jr. scored 32 points to lead Jackson State over Arkansas State 75-71 on Tuesday night. Evans added five rebounds for the Tigers (2-6). Chase Adams scored 10 points, shooting 3 of 8 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line. Derrian Ford led the Red Wolves (2-5) in scoring, finishing with 14 points. Taryn Todd added 12 points and three steals for Arkansas State. In addition, Terrance Ford Jr. had nine points and five assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
